    "template_content": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>NO PURCHASE NECESSARY TO ENTER OR TO WIN. MAKING A PURCHASE WILL NOT IMPROVE YOUR CHANCES OF WINNING. ALL FEDERAL, STATE, LOCAL AND MUNICIPAL LAWS AND REGULATIONS APPLY. VOID WHERE PROHIBITED. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>SPONSOR</u> <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>This Community Choice promotion (the “Promotion”) is sponsored by USA Today Co Media Corp. and its subsidiaries and affiliates, having a principal business address at 1675 Broadway, 23<sup>rd</sup> Floor, New York, New York 10019 (the “Sponsor” or “USA Today Co”).<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>ADMINISTRATOR </u><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>UPICKEM, a contesting platform of Second Street Media, 317 N. 11th Street, Suite 302, St. Louis, Missouri 63101 (the “Administrator”). <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>PROMOTION DESCRIPTION</u><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>There are two (2) parts to this Promotion as follows: <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>(1) <u>Community’s Choice Sweepstakes</u> (the “Sweepstakes”) for the public, which includes a nomination and voting phase; and <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>(2) <u>Community’s Choice Awards</u> (the “Contest”).<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">&nbsp; </span>The Contest is divided into categories (each, a “Category” and collectively, the “Categories”), and businesses, organizations, events, activities, items, products, communities or individuals from the options provided (each a “Candidate” and collectively the “Candidates”) will be placed into a Category by the public as further described below. Candidates and winners in each Category will then be determined by popular vote from the public audience. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>The Sweepstakes and the Contest will together be referred to as the “Promotion”. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>PARTICIPATING PUBLICATIONS</u><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>{{Organization.Name}} (each, the “Publication”, or, collectively, the “Publications”) <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>BUSINESS SPONSORS</u> (if applicable)<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>_______________________________<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>(each the “Business Sponsor” and collectively the “Business Sponsors”) <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>CONTEST AREA</u><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Within 50 miles of the Publication (the “Contest Area”)<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>ENTRANT ELIGIBILITY</u><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Open only to legal residents of the continental United States who are eighteen (18) years of age or older (or the age of majority in his or her state of residence) at the time of voting (each, the “Voter” or collectively the “Voters”).<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">&nbsp; </span>Employees, contractors or interns of the Sponsor and or a Business Sponsor, and each of their respective divisions, affiliates, parent companies, subsidiaries, advertising and promotion agencies (including, in each case, immediate family members) are not eligible to vote in this Promotion.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">&nbsp; </span><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>VOTER ELIGIBILITY</u><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Open only to legal residents of the continental United States who are eighteen (18) years of age or older (or the age of majority in his or her state of residence) at the time of voting (each, the “Voter” or collectively the “Voters”).<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">&nbsp; </span>Employees, contractors or interns of the Sponsor and or a Business Sponsor, and each of their respective divisions, affiliates, parent companies, subsidiaries, advertising and promotion agencies (including, in each case, immediate family members) are not eligible to vote in this Promotion.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">&nbsp; </span><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>IMPORTANT DATES</u> <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>1. NOMINATION PERIOD: Start Date: 12:01 a.m. Local time on {{Promotion.EntryStartDate}} ; End Date: 11:59 p.m. Local time on {{Promotion.EntryEndDate}} (the “Nomination Period”). <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>2. VOTING BALLOT PERIOD: Start Date: 12:01 a.m. Local time on {{Promotion.SelectionStartDate}} ; End Date: 11:59 p.m. Local time on {{Promotion.SelectionEndDate}} (the “Voting Ballot Period”). <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>3. SWEEPSTAKES RANDOM DRAWING DATE (Nomination Round): within 7 - 10 days of {{Promotion.EntryEndDate}} (the “Drawing”). <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>4. SWEEPSTAKES RANDOM DRAWING DATE (Voting Round): within 7 - 10 days of {{Promotion.SelectionEndDate}} (the “Drawing”). <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>PRIZE INFORMATION </u><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>1. NUMBER OF WINNERS SELECTED IN THE DRAWING: One (1) each the “Sweeps Winner”, and, collectively, the “Sweeps Winners”) <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>2. BRIEF DESCRIPTION AND APPROXIMATE RETAIL VALUE (“ARV”) OF PRIZES AWARDED: $250 Gift Card <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>3. SWEEPSTAKES WINNER NOTIFICATION: Each of the Sweeps Winners will be notified within ten (10) days of the Drawing.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">&nbsp; </span><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>SWEEPSTAKES PORTION OF THE PROMOTION</u><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>HOW TO ENTER THE SWEEPSTAKES; SWEEPSTAKES RULES </u><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>1. In order to enter the Sweepstakes or win the prize, the Entrant must comply fully with these Official Rules, and by entering agrees to be bound by these Official Rules and the decisions of USA Today Co, whose decisions shall be binding and final in all respects. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>2. During the Nomination Period, each Entrant must fill out the ballot (the “Ballot” and collectively the “Ballots”) or vote in the Contest portion of this Promotion (each the “Vote” or collectively the “Votes”) as directed. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>3. If applicable to the particular Promotion at the Publication, the Entrant may have the option to submit a “write-in” candidate in a Category (each the “Write-In Candidate”). Because of spelling errors and variations on names, the Sponsor will attempt to match the vote to the correct Candidate, and such decisions are in the sole discretion of the Sponsor. Vague or ambiguous nominations will not be accepted, in the Sponsor’s sole discretion.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">&nbsp; </span>Sponsor reserves the right to disqualify any nominations that it deems offensive or obscene, or that do not comply with the terms of these Official Rules. Sponsor further reserves the right to disqualify any nominated Candidate at the nominated Candidate’s request. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>4. After completing the required number of selections on the Ballot, the Entrant will automatically be registered in the Sweepstakes (each the “Entry” or collectively the “Entries”).<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">&nbsp; </span>All Entries become the property of USA Today Co. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>5. One (1) Ballot/one (1) Category will be accepted during the Nomination Period. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>6. There is no fee to vote in a Category or submit a Ballot.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>7. No Ballots will be accepted after the Ballot Deadline. The Sponsor’s computer is the official time-keeping device for this Promotion. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>8. Ballots will not be accepted through e-mail, facsimile, U.S. Postal Service, other express delivery services, or at the offices of the Publication. Ballots submitted with multiple e-mail addresses, under multiple identities or through the use of any agent or other device to enter multiple times will be deemed invalid. The use of any automated system to submit Ballots is prohibited and will result in disqualification of all such Ballots as well as the Entrant. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>9. In order to be entered in the voting portion of the Promotion, an Entrant must vote in the required number of Categories as specified on the Ballot. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>10. Entrant may be, but is not required to, submit a comment (“Comment”) in connection with the Ballot. The Comment must not contain material that: (a) violates or infringes another’s rights, including but not limited to privacy, publicity or intellectual property rights, or that constitutes copyright infringement; (b) disparages the Sponsor or any other person or party affiliated with the Promotion and administration of this Promotion; (c) was not created by Entrant; (d) is inappropriate, indecent, obscene hateful, tortious, or defamatory; © promotes bigotry, racism, hatred or harm against any group or individual or promotes discrimination based on race, gender, religion, nationality, disability, sexual orientation or age; or (f) is unlawful. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>11. Additional restrictions or requirements may apply to certain Ballot Categories and will be clearly listed on the Ballot. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>VOTING/Nomination RULES</u> <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>1. For purposes of this Promotion, the Vote must be cast by a “unique” voter. A “unique” voter is an individual person: (a) who has registered to vote, (b) with unique registration information (i.e. e-mail address) that is not duplicative of another Voter’s information and (c) that is not created with an intent to hide the identity of the individual or allow Votes by an individual in excess of the limits set forth herein. If Sponsor determines, in its sole discretion, that an abuse of the “unique” voter rules has occurred, the Sponsor may disqualify Votes cast by such Voters, including if more than five (5) of such Voters registered from the same residential computer “IP address”. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>2. The Sponsor reserves the right to refuse votes for Candidates that are deemed not appropriate for the Category for which the Votes were cast. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>3. Vote totals will not be published at any time during the Nomination Period. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>4. Voters are limited to one (1) Vote per Category per day during the Nomination Period. A Candidate may be honored in more than one (1) Category, but Votes will not be combined across Categories. Any Vote attempts above the voting limits set forth above will not be counted as valid. &nbsp;The Sponsor reserves the right to change the above-mentioned limits on the number of Votes that may be made, in its sole discretion. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>5. The Sponsor will not be responsible for misdirected Votes. Ballots and/or Votes generated by a script, macro, or other automated means is prohibited and such Ballots and Votes will be disqualified, in the Sponsor’s sole discretion.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">&nbsp; </span>Any use of robotic, repetitive, automatic, programmed, vote exchange websites, vote “farming” or other method to vote or unfairly increase Votes, as determined by the Sponsor in its sole discretion, is prohibited and will void all such Votes and/or Ballots submitted by that Voter. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>6. The Voters and the Candidates are prohibited from obtaining Votes by any fraudulent or inappropriate means, including, without limitation, offering prizes, cash or other financial considerations, or other inducements to members of the public, as determined by the Sponsor in its sole discretion.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">&nbsp; </span>If the Sponsor concludes, in its sole discretion, that any Candidate has colluded with any Voter to violate these Official Rules or has participated in or actively encouraged such activity, whether directly or indirectly, the Sponsor may disqualify that Candidate and the Voter from further participation in the Contest.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>The Sponsor reserves the right to disqualify any Voter or Candidate from further participation in the Contest if Sponsor concludes, in its sole discretion, that such Voter or Candidate: (a) has attempted to tamper with the voting process or other operation of the Promotion; (b) has disregarded or has attempted to circumvent these Official Rules; or (c) has acted toward the Sponsor or any other Candidate or Voter in an unfair, inequitable, deliberately annoying, threatening, disrupting or harassing manner. If a dispute arises regarding compliance with these Official Rules, the Sponsor may consider, in its sole discretion, data reasonably available to the Sponsor through information technology systems in the Sponsor’s control, but the Sponsor will not be obligated to consider any data or other information collected from any other source. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>7. THE SPONSOR RESERVES THE RIGHT, IN ITS SOLE DISCRETION, TO DISQUALIFY ANY BALLOT OR VOTE AT ANY TIME THAT IN ITS OPINION DOES NOT COMPLY WITH THESE OFFICIAL RULES. If the Sponsor determines, in its sole discretion, that the security, administration, fairness and/or operation of the Promotion has been corrupted or impaired by any non-authorized intervention, network failure, information storage failure , telecommunications failure, malfunction, or any other cause beyond the Sponsor’s control, the Sponsor may terminate the Promotion. If the Sponsor terminates the Promotion, the Sponsor will post notice of same and select the winners in each Category by applying the criteria set forth above based on eligible, non-suspect Votes received as of such termination date. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>ENTRY INFORMATION; COMMUNICATIONS; OPT-OUT. </u><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>As a condition of entering the Sweepstakes, each Entrant gives consent for the Sponsor to obtain, process, store and deliver his or her name, address and other collected information to the Sponsor and to the Sponsor’s service providers and business partners: (i) for the purpose of administering this Promotion; (ii) to comply with applicable laws, regulations and rules; and (iii) to communicate with Entrant about offers and promotions from the Sponsor and the Sponsor’s affiliates and/or business partners. Any information Entrant provides to the Sponsor may be used to communicate with the Entrant in relation to this Promotion and/or for the other purposes specified herein. Collection and use of personally identifiable information will be in accordance with the Sponsor’s Privacy Policy or the applicable business partner’s privacy policy. Any email communication from the Sponsor, Administrator, its service providers and/or its business partners will contain an <i>Unsubscribe</i> link enabling the Entrant to opt-out of further communications (except for Promotion administration if Entrant continues to participate after unsubscribing).<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">&nbsp; </span>The Entrant may request deletion of his/her account by e-mailing the Sponsor at promotionshelp@usatventures.com and following the instructions provided. An Entrant’s choice to opt out will not affect the submission of a Vote or Ballot in this Promotion. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>ODDS OF WINNING </u><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Odds of winning depend on the total number of Entries received and how the Entries meet the criteria established for the Sweepstakes portion of this Promotion. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>SWEEPS WINNER NOTIFICATION </u><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Each of the Sweeps Winners will be notified by phone and/or e-mail within ten (10) business days of the Drawing in accordance with the contact information supplied at the time of entry. If these methods fail after one (1) week, the Sponsor will select an alternate winner in a random drawing from all remaining eligible Entries, according to the criteria established in these Official Rules. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>REQUIRED DOCUMENTATION </u><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Each of the potential Sweeps Winners may be required to submit an affidavit of eligibility/release of liability/prize acceptance agreement (collectively, the “Affidavit”) where permitted and return the Affidavit, properly executed, within the time period specified at notification before being eligible to receive any prize(s). If any potential Sweeps Winner fails or refuses to sign and return such Affidavit within the time period required by Sponsor, submits a falsified or fraudulent Affidavit, or if the prize or prize notification is returned as rejected, faulty, unclaimed or returned as undeliverable to such potential Sweeps Winner, such potential Sweeps Winner may be disqualified and an alternate may be selected in a random drawing, in Sponsor’s sole determination. Non-compliance with these Official Rules shall result in disqualification and award of the prize(s) to an alternate winner in accordance with these Official Rules. Sponsor is not responsible for and shall not be liable for late, lost, damaged, intercepted, misdirected, or unsuccessful efforts to notify a potential Sweeps Winner.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">&nbsp; </span>Any potential Sweeps Winner is subject to verification and the potential Sweeps Winner’s full compliance with these Official Rules before any prize will be awarded.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Once eligibility has been verified and the Sponsor receives the Sweeps Winner’s requested information, the Sponsor will arrange to award the prize.<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>PRIZE CONDITIONS AND GIFT CARDS </u><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>No substitution or transfer of the prize will be allowed, except at the sole discretion of USA Today Co.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">&nbsp; </span>USA Today Co reserves the right to substitute prizes of equal or greater value.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>The prize has no cash value and may not be redeemed for cash at any time.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">&nbsp; </span>Any Sweeps Winner who fails to pick up the prize within thirty (30) days from the date of winning for any reason, and fails to obtain an extension from the Sponsor or make alternate arrangements with the Sponsor, will forfeit the prize. The Sponsor reserves the right, in its sole discretion, to award unclaimed prizes to alternate Entrants or not to award the unclaimed prizes. No compensation will be given for lost, stolen, mutilated or expired gift cards. The Sponsor is not responsible for replacing lost, stolen, mutilated or expired gift cards. Fulfillment of gift cards is the sole responsibility of the merchant, not the Sponsor, and is only redeemable at the specified locations. The gift card must be surrendered upon redemption and no photocopies or reproductions will be honored. All gift cards are subject to the terms and conditions regarding use, loss, theft, and redemption and all other terms and conditions established by the merchant providing that gift card. Any questions or issues regarding gift cards must be directed to the merchant customer service center, and will be handled exclusively by the merchant. All transactions, disputes, questions, and all other aspects of the relationship between any prize winner and merchant are solely the responsibility of the prize winner and merchant, and the Sponsor and its affiliates have no responsibility for any such matters. The Sponsor has not made and the Sponsor is not responsible in any manner for any warranties, representations or guarantees, express or implied, in fact or law, relating to the gift cards, regarding the use, value or enjoyment of the gift cards, including, without limitation, merchantability or fitness for a particular purpose.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>No compensation will be given for lost, stolen, mutilated or expired tickets. USA Today Co shall not be responsible for any cancelling or rescheduling of any event. Fulfillment of any tickets is the sole responsibility of the venue, not USA Today Co. It is illegal to scalp any tickets won from USA Today Co. If a prize winner is caught scalping tickets, he or she will be ejected from the venue and this will result in the winner’s disqualification from this and all future USA Today Co sweepstakes and contests. The resale or auction of USA Today Co prizes or tickets will result in the winner’s disqualification from all future USA Today Co sweepstakes and contests.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>If, due to a printing, production or other error, more prizes are claimed than are intended to be awarded per the above, the intended prizes will be awarded in a random drawing from among all verified and validated prize claims. In no event will more than the stated number of prizes be awarded. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>TAXES </u><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>All local, state and federal taxes incurred by accepting a prize will be the sole responsibility of the prize winner. Any person winning over $600 in prizes during any one (1) year period will receive an IRS Form 1099 at the end of the calendar year, and a copy of such form will be filed with the IRS. <o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>CONTEST PORTION OF THE PROMOTION</u><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>CANDIDATE ELIGIBILITY</u><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>1. The Candidate must have a physical location in the Contest Area of the State, or, in the case of individuals, perform services in the Contest Area of the State.<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>2. If the Candidate is a licensed profession as defined under the laws of the State and uses a professional title as defined by the State’s laws, the Candidate may be required to provide a copy of the active license (the “License”) within five (5) business days from USA Today Co’s request. If the Candidate does not provide the License within the requisite time frame, the Candidate may be disqualified, in USA Today Co’s sole and absolute discretion. If USA Today Co determines that the Candidate’s License is not applicable to the Category, USA Today Co may remove the Candidate from the Promotion, or place the Candidate in a different Category. Any and all decisions by USA Today Co regarding Candidate placement in a Category or removal from a Category shall be final and binding in all respects.<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>3. The Candidate must not be past due on any financial obligations with USA Today Co.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>4.&nbsp; If the Candidate is an individual, such Candidate may be disqualified if he or she partakes in any activity or act that, in USA Today Co’s reasonable judgment, (a) tends to bring the Candidate into public disrepute, contempt, scandal, or ridicule, or tends to shock insult, or offend the majority of the consuming public or any protected class or group; and/or (b) may in any way injure or adversely reflect on the name, goodwill or reputation of USA Today Co, their affiliates, or respective products, logos or trademarks, including, without limitation, being arrested, charged with or convicted of substance abuse or DWI, a felony or misdemeanor, or crime of moral turpitude, or charged with a fraud (“Negative Acts”). If the Candidate commits any of the Negative Acts, USA Today Co shall have the right, in their sole and absolute discretion, to disqualify such Candidate, without any further obligation or liability to the Candidate.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>5.&nbsp; USA Today Co reserves the right, in their sole determination, to refuse or otherwise restrict a Candidate’s &nbsp;eligibility to participate in the Promotion for any reason.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u>HOW CANDIDATE WINNERS ARE CHOSEN </u><o:p></o:p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>The leading Vote recipients in each Category will be declared the finalists (collectively the “Candidate Finalists”).<span style=\"mso-spac